@bolkedebruin you were quite right. I was trying to use the existing execution_date argument set up for use with other airflow [command] calls, but this is set as a required positional parameter for these calls. As such I've had to call the parameter "exec_date" instead. When I tried to set it up with the verbose flag: 
"--execution_date" I still got an error, so I tried the verbose flag "--exec_date" instead. This then worked, but showed up that I'd missed the pass through calls in the api/client folder, which I've now fixed. Tests are passing. LandscapeIO is unhappy, but seems to have picked up issues in files that I've not touched and none new in the files that I have touched. As such, I'm not intending to fix the issues it says I've introduced.
Unless you have any further comments, I believe this is ready to merge.

@genomics-geek , I actually have new set of ssh_hook along with ssh_operator,  I will look into this to see how it can be merged and I will add commit here.

@sdikby,
1) I will make sure we continue support the tunnel feature with new ssh_hooks or ssh_operator.
2) I think its good feature to have regex for filtering while transferring files. I will look into it, Thanks for suggestion.
